msgstr ""

#: ../../src/cve/2010-2234.rst:32
msgid ""
"Apache CouchDB versions prior to version :ref:`0.11.1 <release/0.11.1>` are "
"vulnerable to `Cross Site Request Forgery`_ (CSRF) attacks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/cve/2010-2234.rst:38
msgid "Mitigation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/cve/2010-2234.rst:40
msgid ""
"All users should upgrade to CouchDB :ref:`0.11.2 <release/0.11.2>` or "
":ref:`1.0.1 <release/1.0.1>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/cve/2010-2234.rst:43
msgid ""
"Upgrades from the :ref:`0.11.x <release/0.11.x>` and :ref:`0.10.x "
"<release/0.10.x>` series should be seamless."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/cve/2010-2234.rst:46
msgid "Users on earlier versions should consult with upgrade notes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/cve/2010-2234.rst:49
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/cve/2010-2234.rst:51
msgid ""
"A malicious website can `POST` arbitrary JavaScript code to well known "
"CouchDB installation URLs (like http://localhost:5984/) and make the browser"
" execute the injected JavaScript in the security context of CouchDB's admin "
"interface Futon."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/cve/2010-2234.rst:56
msgid ""
"Unrelated, but in addition the JSONP API has been turned off by default to "
"avoid potential information leakage."
msgstr ""

